texts.text: My temple is tending to Lady Apsaras.
She's badly hurt but will survive.
Thank goodness! Big Sis Apsaras is saved!
Now we can talk this out.
So, let's cut to the chase. It looks like Indrajit is back.
Indrajit...
I did some research after we fought him the first time,
and the name "Indra" pops up in multiple books...
It's obvious you two got a history.
A history?
Let's save the explanations and return to the point at hand.
You probably have questions, but we need a strong demon ally.
Will you lend us your power?
A "strong" ally...
I don't know how helpful I'll be in my current state.
I haven't reigned supreme in ages.
My power from then and now is like night and day.
For real?
...Still, Apsaras has faith in your power.
We wanna believe too. Please.
Lend us your strength.
Are you chicken?
We're asking for a favor here. Let's not instigate him.
People once worshipped me as the perfect warrior.
I was a champion who defended the weak and lent aid to all.
That sentiment has not changed.
It is my duty to protect those like you who seek my assistance.
I shall help you subdue Indrajit.
You're a lifesaver, Indra.
Wow, he agreed to it faster than I expected.
*Wince*
Are you okay, Megakin?!
Please don't push yourself. You're hurt.
Haha, can't argue that.
We're all beat. Let's pick this up tomorrow.
Sorry for the ruckus, Kouki.
*Chuckle* Don't sweat it.
You might be a Liberator, but I admire your drive, Megakin.
Right back at ya. I heard about the match in two days.
Oh...
It's a powerhouse-packed mixed martial arts tournament.
Every streamer is talkin' about it. You're gonna enter, yeah?
Your career has changed, but your showboatin' sure hasn't.
...Y-Yeah. I guess so.
(? Kouki...)
Well, thanks for lettin' us stay over. See ya tomorrow.
Yeah, later.
Huh? You're still here, Jeng Yun?
I'm not tired yet. Besides...
Don't you have something on your mind, Kouki?
Huh?
You seemed off today.
I'm here to talk if you don't mind.
Heh, I'm no match for you.
I think I'll announce my retirement at this next tournament.
Retirement?! Why?
I'm not young anymore. My body is falling apart.
I think I'll quit for good and take over the temple.
But...you breezed through this morning's workout.
It's too soon to give up.
I wanted to hear the fans' cheers one last time.
So, I switched to a trendy sport like MMA, but it wasn't enough.
It hit me recently.
I've just been clinging to my past glory.
I've grown hopelessly pathetic...
Kouki...
Are you really fine with that?
Oh...
Don't you wish to rise again, Kouki?
Lord Indra...
I protect this vast world while keeping an eye on humanity.
Especially faithful disciples like yourself.
So, I can easily read what is in your heart.
You say you cling to past glories, but I disagree.
That is just an excuse.
An excuse...
Yes. Attachments can bind the heart, but for you it is an escape.
You'll only suffer regret if you limit yourself and run away.
No, I've simply accepted reality.
There's no denying I've grown too feeble to beat anyone...
>Kouki trudges away.
Kouki...
Fool. How can an uncertain heart hope to reach enlightenment?
Hmph!
>Suddenly, Indra glances toward an empty thicket.
What's the matter, Indra?
...It's nothing.
You should return as well. I have business to attend to.
Understood.
I'll see you tomorrow.
Eek! Someone save me!
What's the matter? Aren't you going to finish the job?
That attack just now was pretty good. For a human, anyway.
No... Don't kill me...
As a sacrificial lamb, you should feel honored.
>The man is killed by a blade to the heart.
Yes, this is...
>A lust for battle rises within Indrajit.
Quite excellent.
Such a robust sacrifice is undoubtedly most ideal.
Lord Indrajit!
You're back. How did it go?
I looked into it as you instructed. I'll lead you there now!
Wait.
Hmph! It's you...
It's been a while, Meganada.
Or should I call you "Indrajit"?
Indra...
